1.3 Licensee
"Licensee" means any individual, company, organization, institution, government
entity, educational institution, or other legal or natural person that receives
or uses the Software.

1.4 Commercial Use
Commercial Use means any activity that directly or indirectly generates revenue,
commercial value, business advantage, competitive advantage, customer
acquisition, or financial benefit.
Commercial Use includes, without limitation:
- selling the Software;
- licensing the Software;
- sublicensing the Software;
- providing paid services using the Software;
- offering Software-as-a-Service (SaaS);
- offering Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS);
- offering cloud-hosted services;
- providing APIs;
- managed hosting;
- consulting services primarily based upon the Software;
- enterprise deployment;
- integration into commercial products;
- internal business operations of a for-profit entity;
- monetized websites or applications;
- paid support services;
- training sold for profit where the Software constitutes a substantial
  component.

1.5 Non-Commercial Use
Non-Commercial Use means personal learning, academic research, classroom
education, private experimentation, security research, evaluation of the Software
for up to ninety (90) days by any entity, and any other use that does not
directly or indirectly produce commercial benefit. For clarity, the 90-day
evaluation period for commercial entities is considered Non-Commercial Use.

1.6 Modification
"Modification" means any alteration, enhancement, translation, adaptation,
refactoring, optimization, extension, bug fix, or derivative work created from
the Software.

1.7 Distribution
"Distribution" means making the Software available to any third party by any
means including publication, download, transfer, hosting, physical media, or
network transmission.

1.8 Fork
"Fork" means a copy of the Software repository created using Git or any
equivalent version control system for the purpose of development or contribution.

1.9 Contribution
"Contribution" means any code, documentation, translation, issue, patch, artwork,
dataset, model, test, suggestion, or other material intentionally submitted to
Fiavo for inclusion in the Software.

1.10 Intellectual Property Rights
Intellectual Property Rights include copyrights, patents, trademarks, trade
secrets, database rights, design rights, and any similar legal protections
recognized under applicable law.

1.11 Written Permission
Written Permission means explicit authorization issued by Fiavo in writing,
including signed agreements or electronic communications from officially
authorized Fiavo representatives.

1.12 Commercial License
Commercial License means a separate written agreement executed by Fiavo granting
rights beyond those provided under this License.

1.13 Startup Entity
"Startup Entity" means a for-profit legal entity with fewer than ten (10)
employees and annual gross revenue of less than $1,000,000 USD (or equivalent).

